@ThinkingandTinkering Cheers for that mate. The paper is behind a paywall so I'll just have to purchase it.

The situation with copper I oxide Vs copper II oxide and calculating it might make for a good video on the topic. I have run into a similar situation with making iron III chloride. I had a known amount of iron nails and used an known amount of HCL (30%) to make iron II chloride. I was then faced with trying to work out how much H2O2 (30%) to use to covert it to iron III chloride. In the end I just used an excess of H2O2 and let it sit for a couple weeks for the H2O2 to decompose.

Anyway, thanks for the great vid.

